rComments: Ahmed is pretty entertaining! I find he takes everything SUPER personally and isn't the most understanding when it comes to mistakes made in the virtual setting. Make sure you read the instructions on assignments because he will ROAST you if you make one small error in handing something in.

One of the very few profs who actually empathises with students. Genuinely nice person and teaches lectures clearly. Loves answering questions. Exams and assignments are easy as long as you pay attention in the lectures. Deadlines are fair and he always has office hours for clarification. Consider HK lucky to have Ahmed as the stats prof!

Best prof I've ever had. I'm not the biggest fan of math but he honestly made me love the subject. I wish he could teach all my classes lol. Make sure you attend all the lectures which shouldn't be an issue because he is so entertaining!! If you get him as a prof consider yourself lucky

Hands down the best professor I have ever had. Wouldn't mind if my other professors had the same passion and dedication that he brings to the classroom. I have never had a professor so inclined to make sure his students had help every step of the way. Exam was not as straight forward as his assignments so study hard.
Just a wonderful human. Extremely caring and generous with his time, but also seems to be such a genuine person. Confident and competent. Also great sense of humour and fashion :P
Probably the best prof I've ever had, no joke.

Great teacher and great person. Listen to him and engage in class, you should be fine. Exams and assignments are consistent with class material, but time will be an issue on exams (the only real thing that makes it kinda hard). ALWAYS wants to help and he is good at it, so take advantage of this great prof! One of a kind

Cares a lot about his students' success, available during office hours and he organized a review session on his free time before the final. Very fair grading and material on the midterm and the final. Great prof!

By far the best prof I've ever had. He absolutely loves teaching and cares so much about his students' success. Because it is a math-based course, it requires some effort, but Ahmed gives you every opportunity to get an A+. Would recommend him and this course to anybody, even as an elective.

Statistics are never interesting, but he certainly makes this class as bearable as it could possibly be. Even if you're not great at math, the way he teaches makes everything easy to understand. You have to go over practice problems to understand sometimes, but that's the way it is with math. Don't talk in his class though or he'll kick you out.

He was a great prof. You really have to be quiet in class or he will get distracted and mad. When the class is quiet, he is very clear and uses good examples. His tests actually test you on what he taught and are very fair. He made stats interesting. Don't buy the textbook.

He is definitely passionate about helping students... and having a quite classroom. His office hours really helped   for anything you didn't get in class. Don't bother with the text book, he provides everything in the lecture slides and you can youtube it if you still don't understand.

Such an amazing professor! Not sure what some reviews are talking about because he was so good at explaining the material. I got an A+ and the only reason I opened the book was because I missed a couple classes and wanted clarification on those topics. If you struggle with math then you may have trouble but he is absolutely great!
Amazing professor! He is so passionate about teaching and conveys the material very effectively. Extremely helpful and quick at responding to questions over email.

He is a very passionate guy, but despite many efforts to clarify the topics the concepts were never clearly identified... You will definitely need the text book and a lot of focus to get through this course

Ahmed is VERY passionate about his teaching. HOWEVER, not all of us are meant to be teachers / have the ability to convey material in a way that caters to most students. A simple subject became extremely difficult, and he had a hard time answering any questions. Again, passionate but not a good professor.

Ahmed is an excellent teacher. He definitely facilitated my learning experience statistics. He conveys the matter effectively, expects ALL his students to learn, do well & succeed, and all his evaluations (assignments, midterm & exam) are fair. What more do you want from a prof? Unlike some profs he cares A LOT! He's almost passionate to a fault.

Gets very emotional in class if someone is talking, even if its about the class. Though he is very helpful at his office hours, and the assignments and mid term were more than fair. If you can bare a few rants from the guy hes a pretty solid professor.
AMAZING. His passion and dedication to his students are unmatched!
